The paper deals with transfer learning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (AI) research. The use of Bayesian models and causal theory induction suggests that the paper may fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves learning and modeling, which are common themes in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of a model-based planner suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves the transfer of knowledge between different environments, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
